    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br>
Strategy  <br>
There are a few new cards in here so let me explain those first in order to reveal the strategery <--(thank you G BUSH) I lowered my cout to forty! aren&#39;t you all happy!<br>
<br>
Fossik, ringsmith: starting energy 12, energize 6, power strengthen- discard a card from your hand to add two energy to any one of your creatures <br>
**nifty heh?** <br>
<br>
Strag&#39;s Claws <br>
2 energy relic that allows you to add one energy to your attacking creatures before and after energy is removed! mwaa haaa haaa! do you feel its power?! **fast growing fungus** <br>
<br>
Crushing Fungus (or fungus amungus) <br>
4 energy spell *and my new best friend* choose any one creature in play. discard four energy from that creature if this discards the chosen creature that creatures magi does not energize his or her next turn. only underneath and underneath shadow magi may play this spell. <br>
<br>
Muggum (the poor man&#39;s tunnel hyren) <br>
1 energy bograth/underneath creature. Power-burrow. Discard muggum from play and choose two underneath and or bograth creatures in play. until the end of your next turn, those creatures are burrowed. yeah burrow is good...i like this mushroom. <br>
<br>
so back to the deck. <br>
this deck works by burrowing your creatures and attacking! big surprise with underneath hey? if you have more thunderquakes feel free to replace a few bottomless pits. <br>
<br>
The muggums are great for protecting your parmalags and syres while they gaina bit of energy from the boots. <br>
<br>
the strags claws give a serious edge to this deck epecially with this combo.I love them sooo much! <br>
<br>
strag&#39;s claws+burrowed parmalags+plus parmalags power+aglow=ouch oh pain! pain! pain! <br>
YOur paramalags gain massive amount of energy! <br>
<br>
Also with the Syre&#39;s, Agovo&#39;s and tomorrows jewel it is easy to gain card advantage. plus with the great crushing fungus you can easliy gain energy advantage (not to mention two bomb magi with high energize rates) <br>
<br>
Poor Radget has never made it out onto the field do to the awsome fuidness this deck seems to possess try it out on an opponent near you! <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Sidar the Inferno <br>
Local Madman of Cald, <br>
Lover of Fungus  <br>
